s, guided walks, lectures, panels, screenings, performances, publications, and exhibitions, a public research trajectory is being developed within the framework of <em>Deep Time Chicago<\/em>, offering a variety of formats where inhabitants of the Chicago area can grapple with the crucial questions of global ecological change.<\/p>\n ","post_title":"Deep Time Chicago","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"deep-time-chicago","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2020-07-03 15:00:43","post_modified_gmt":"2020-07-03 13:00:43","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/?post_type=project&#038;p=4955","menu_order":0,"post_type":"project","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","author_name":"anujah.fernando","permalink":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/project\/deep-time-chicago\/","acf":{"thumbnail":{"ID":9404,"id":9404,"title":"DeepTimeChicago_keyvisual_crop","filename":"DeepTimeChicago_keyvisual_crop.jpg","filesize":26605,"url":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/DeepTimeChicago_keyvisual_crop.jpg","link":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/project\/deep-time-chicago\/deeptimechicago_keyvisual_crop\/","alt":"","author":"37","description":"Image by United States Geological Survey","caption":"Geological Time Spiral","name":"deeptimechicago_keyvisual_crop","status":"inherit","uploaded_to":4955,"date":"2019-09-13 09:02:50","modified":"2019-09-13 10:01:16","menu_order":0,"mime_type":"image\/jpeg","type":"image","subtype":"jpeg","icon":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-includes\/images\/media\/default.png","width":500,"height":252,"sizes":{"thumbnail":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/DeepTimeChicago_keyvisual_crop-150x150.jpg","thumbnail-width":150,"thumbnail-height":150,"medium":"https: